fix: cache, cluster, engine connections, and DDG web results

Cache (PART 9):
- Rewrite ResultCache to wrap cache.Cache interface (memory/Valkey backend)
- Use JSON serialisation so results are backend-portable
- Key naming follows PART 9 convention: search:{hash}
- Replace bare int64 counters with sync/atomic.Int64
- AggregatorConfig.Cache replaces MaxCacheSize; auto-falls back to memory

Cluster (PART 10):
- Node states: healthy / degraded / offline / removed (was online/offline only)
- Stale thresholds: healthy→degraded at 90s, degraded→offline at 5min
- Primary election: lowest node ID wins (was joined_at order)
- hashToken: use crypto/sha256 (was broken byte-copy)

Engine connection exhaustion (ERR_CONNECTION_TIMED_OUT):
- Add shared http.Transport (MaxIdleConns 200, MaxIdleConnsPerHost 20,
  IdleConnTimeout 90s) in transport.go; all 20 engines now share it
- Replace Body.Read(buf) single-chunk partial reads in google.go (4×)
  and duckduckgo.go (1×) with io.ReadAll(io.LimitReader) so TCP
  connections are fully drained and eligible for reuse by the transport

DuckDuckGo general search results:
- Replace Instant Answer API (api.duckduckgo.com) with HTML endpoint
  (html.duckduckgo.com/html) — the Instant Answer API only returns
  category/disambiguation pages (duckduckgo.com/c/...), not web results
- Parse real web results from HTML using result__a / result__snippet
- Decode DDG redirect URLs (uddg= param) to actual destination URLs
